    "created_at": "2015-07-06T23:07:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-07T00:03:34Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The point of `TargetableUnit.GetTargetableTypes()` is to separate the upgrade logic from subclasses. As long as the upgrade logic works for TargetableUnit and the enabled behavior of subclasses work, then the subclasses should also have the correct disabled behavaior.\n\nThat said, `TargetableAircraft` and `TargetableSubmarine` can be tested for correct disabled behavior by adding a nonempty dummy `UpgradeTypes` (such as `UpgradeTypes: dummy_upgrade`) and `UpgradeMinEnabledLevel: 1` to any `TargetableAircraft` and `TargetableSubmarine`.\n\nExample that disables `TargetableAircraft` and `TargetableSubmarine` in the ra mod:\n\n``` diff\ndiff --git a/mods/ra/rules/defaults.yaml b/mods/ra/rules/defaults.yaml\nindex 2807979..fb9e8f3 100644\n--- a/mods/ra/rules/defaults.yaml\n+++ b/mods/ra/rules/defaults.yaml\n@@ -304,6 +304,8 @@\n    TargetableAircraft:\n        TargetTypes: Air\n        GroundedTargetTypes: Ground, Repair\n+       UpgradeTypes: dummy_upgrade\n+       UpgradeMinEnabledLevel: 1\n    HiddenUnderFog:\n        Type: CenterPosition\n    AttackMove:\ndiff --git a/mods/ra/rules/ships.yaml b/mods/ra/rules/ships.yaml\nindex 88a30d1..4057867 100644\n--- a/mods/ra/rules/ships.yaml\n+++ b/mods/ra/rules/ships.yaml\n@@ -23,6 +23,8 @@ SS:\n    TargetableSubmarine:\n        TargetTypes: Ground, Water, Repair\n        CloakedTargetTypes: Underwater, Repair\n+       UpgradeTypes: dummy_upgrade\n+       UpgradeMinEnabledLevel: 1\n    Cloak:\n        CloakTypes: Underwater\n        InitialDelay: 0\n@@ -72,6 +74,8 @@ MSUB:\n    TargetableSubmarine:\n        TargetTypes: Ground, Water, Repair\n        CloakedTargetTypes: Underwater, Repair\n+       UpgradeTypes: dummy_upgrade\n+       UpgradeMinEnabledLevel: 1\n    Cloak:\n        CloakTypes: Underwater\n        InitialDelay: 0\n```\n\nThe planes fly with impunity on the shellmap.\n"
  },
